00:09:33,215 --> 00:09:36,381
- Mr. Solano, well...
- _

268
00:09:36,383 --> 00:09:38,551
He's banned you from the hotel, ma'am.

269
00:09:38,553 --> 00:09:40,521
Hmm. Did he?

270
00:09:40,523 --> 00:09:42,657
And what is your name?

271
00:09:42,659 --> 00:09:43,892
Gabriel.

272
00:09:43,894 --> 00:09:45,394
Excellent.

273
00:09:45,396 --> 00:09:47,530
Gabriel, can you tell
me exactly what he said?

274
00:09:47,532 --> 00:09:49,098
Great, as long as he got the money,

275
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,365
I want out of this whole mess.

276
00:09:51,367 --> 00:09:53,398
And clearly, use discretion

277
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:55,531
when wiring the last of it
so nothing can be traced.

278
00:09:55,533 --> 00:09:57,333
So you think he knows
where his father is?

279
00:09:59,705 --> 00:10:00,772
Just let me know if anything changes.

280
00:10:00,774 --> 00:10:02,639
Yeah. So we're all good.

281
00:10:02,641 --> 00:10:04,307
All right. Bye-bye.

282
00:10:04,309 --> 00:10:05,573
Hey.

283
00:10:05,575 --> 00:10:07,307
Hey...

284
00:10:07,309 --> 00:10:09,041
What was that all about?

285
00:10:09,043 --> 00:10:10,542
Uh, Luisa.

286
00:10:10,544 --> 00:10:11,910
I have to get her out of the hospital,

287
00:10:11,912 --> 00:10:13,611
but I need the power of attorney.

288
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,813
This was absolutely true.

289
00:10:15,814 --> 00:10:18,320
_

290
00:10:18,321 --> 00:10:20,652
- _
- I have to make another call

291
00:10:20,654 --> 00:10:22,153
about it, actually.

292
00:10:22,155 --> 00:10:23,555
Yeah. I have to get to work.

293
00:10:23,557 --> 00:10:25,258
Yeah, uh, we have a meeting, so...

294
00:10:25,260 --> 00:10:26,693
- Okay.
- Okay.

295
00:10:26,695 --> 00:10:28,735
- I'll see you.
- Mm-hmm.

296
00:10:31,128 --> 00:10:32,762
Hello, Jane.

297
00:10:32,764 --> 00:10:34,731
Oh, hi.

298
00:10:34,733 --> 00:10:36,133
I thought you left.

299
00:10:36,135 --> 00:10:37,569
Oh, I did.

300
00:10:37,571 --> 00:10:39,172
But I'm back.

301
00:10:42,175 --> 00:10:43,574
What are you doing here, Petra?

302
00:10:43,576 --> 00:10:44,942
I banned you from this hotel.

303
00:10:44,944 --> 00:10:46,343
Hmm, yes, I know.

304
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:47,576
The manager, uh...

305
00:10:47,578 --> 00:10:48,977
Gabriel was his name, right?

306
00:10:48,979 --> 00:10:50,177
Yeah, anyway, he told me.

307
00:10:50,179 --> 00:10:51,778
Then I fired him.

308
00:10:51,780 --> 00:10:53,979
Consider it my first act
as co-owner of the Marbella.

309
00:10:53,981 --> 00:10:55,480
What?

310
00:10:55,482 --> 00:10:58,049
Oh, didn't you know?

311
00:10:58,051 --> 00:10:59,750
Yes, well...

312
00:10:59,752 --> 00:11:02,153
The company that bought into
the hotel, Stanwyk Investments...

313
00:11:02,155 --> 00:11:03,353
It's a family company.

314
00:11:03,355 --> 00:11:07,019
My old boyfriend's family.

315
00:11:07,021 --> 00:11:09,558
And, well, he bought it for me.

316
00:11:10,761 --> 00:11:13,159
So we need to talk
about some changes, hmm?

317
00:11:13,161 --> 00:11:15,160
The hotel's reputation has taken a hit.

318
00:11:15,162 --> 00:11:17,531
And I believe that the first step

319
00:11:17,533 --> 00:11:19,165
towards changing public perception is

320
00:11:19,167 --> 00:11:21,033
to distance ourselves
from the Solano name.

321
00:11:21,035 --> 00:11:23,471
Meaning, stripping you from
your day-to-day responsibilities.

322
00:11:23,473 --> 00:11:25,239
What are you talking about, Petra?

323
00:11:25,241 --> 00:11:29,506
I believe the term is "silent partner."

324
00:11:30,007 --> 00:11:31,508
Shh...

325
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:34,414
This man, Emilio Solano,

326
00:11:34,416 --> 00:11:36,917
is potentially armed and dangerous.

327
00:11:36,919 --> 00:11:38,686
If anyone sees or hears anything...

328
00:11:38,688 --> 00:11:41,222
So listen, we need to have a
meeting asap about your shower.

329
00:11:41,224 --> 00:11:42,824
Okay, don't make a big thing about it.

330
00:11:42,826 --> 00:11:45,386
I'm gonna make a big thing about it.

331
00:11:46,730 --> 00:11:48,363
That's it.

332
00:11:48,365 --> 00:11:50,799
Just keep your eyes open.

333
00:11:50,801 --> 00:11:53,402
Thank you.

334
00:11:55,506 --> 00:11:56,773
I'm sorry about that.

335
00:11:56,775 --> 00:11:58,576
Jane, I meant it before.

336
00:11:58,578 --> 00:11:59,845
Emilio might try to reach out to his son,

337
00:11:59,847 --> 00:12:01,813
and if he does, we need to know.

338
00:12:01,815 --> 00:12:03,347
Great, as long as he got the money,

339
00:12:03,349 --> 00:12:05,485
I want out of this mess.

340
00:12:05,487 --> 00:12:07,421
What is it?

341
00:12:07,423 --> 00:12:09,089
- Nothing.
- Jane.

342
00:12:09,091 --> 00:12:11,390
This isn't about Rafael
or you or me, okay?

343
00:12:11,392 --> 00:12:12,555
It's about this.

344
00:12:12,557 --> 00:12:13,523
Ugh.

345
00:12:13,525 --> 00:12:14,788
Roman Zazo was murdered.

346
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:16,155
And his killer is still out there.

347
00:12:16,157 --> 00:12:20,461
So be careful, okay?

348
00:12:20,463 --> 00:12:23,728
It should be noted that Jane's
first thought was Rafael.

349
00:12:23,730 --> 00:12:25,829
She really needed to talk to him.

350
00:12:25,831 --> 00:12:28,031
- _
- But then this happened.

351
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:30,032
No one knows you're here, okay?

352
00:12:30,034 --> 00:12:31,898
- _
- Get some rest.

353
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:35,432
Okay, that absolutely did
not mean he was hiding Emilio.

354
00:12:37,934 --> 00:12:40,401
And it's certainly not
like Jane should get

355
00:12:40,403 --> 00:12:42,402
the master key and break in.

356
00:12:42,404 --> 00:12:43,871
That would be ridiculous.

357
00:12:43,873 --> 00:12:46,843
And dangerous.

358
00:12:46,845 --> 00:12:48,477
She should definitely leave.

359
00:12:48,479 --> 00:12:50,777
Right now.

360
00:12:50,779 --> 00:12:53,480
But there's no harm in knocking, right?

361
00:12:57,952 --> 00:12:59,589
Did you forget something?

362
00:13:09,936 --> 00:13:11,571
Jane.

363
00:13:11,573 --> 00:13:12,672
Michael, hi.

364
00:13:12,674 --> 00:13:14,207
A-are you okay? What's wrong?

365
00:13:14,209 --> 00:13:15,409
Nothing.

366
00:13:15,411 --> 00:13:16,510
You always look away

367
00:13:16,512 --> 00:13:17,846
when you're not telling the truth.

368
00:13:17,848 --> 00:13:19,615
I just was... I was looking for Rafael.

369
00:13:19,617 --> 00:13:21,016
And you look scared.

370
00:13:21,018 --> 00:13:22,951
Is this about his father, about the case?

371
00:13:22,953 --> 00:13:25,553
Jane.

372
00:13:25,555 --> 00:13:27,123
Roman Zazo's murderer is on the loose.

373
00:13:27,125 --> 00:13:29,259
But I just saw him.

374
00:13:30,528 --> 00:13:32,562
Hi, Michael.

375
00:13:32,564 --> 00:13:34,331
Hi, Jane.

376
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:35,933
Hi.

377
00:13:38,536 --> 00:13:40,303
What the hell is going on?

378
00:13:41,405 --> 00:13:43,509
I'm Aaron Zazo.

379
00:13:43,511 --> 00:13:45,311
- Aaron?
- Yeah.

380
00:13:45,313 --> 00:13:47,411
I'm Roman's twin brother.

381
00:13:48,947 --> 00:13:51,549
I'm so sorry I scared you.

382
00:13:51,551 --> 00:13:53,651
I figured you were someone
who knew my brother,

383
00:13:53,653 --> 00:13:55,554
but I didn't know who you were.

384
00:13:55,556 --> 00:13:57,490
Oh, yeah, no big deal.

385
00:13:57,492 --> 00:14:00,528
I used to have sisters that are twins.

386
00:14:00,530 --> 00:14:02,964
One of them has a bigger
dimple, I think, maybe.

387
00:14:02,966 --> 00:14:04,600
Look, start at the beginning.

388
00:14:04,602 --> 00:14:06,301
What is going on?

389
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:09,102
After Zaz died, I knew I
had to find his brother.

390
00:14:09,104 --> 00:14:10,736
But they hadn't spoken in years,

391
00:14:10,738 --> 00:14:12,334
and I didn't know where to start.

392
00:14:12,336 --> 00:14:14,502
So I hired a private investigator,

393
00:14:14,504 --> 00:14:16,636
and eventually I tracked
Aaron down to an orphanage

394
00:14:16,638 --> 00:14:18,468
in Mexico where he volunteered.

395
00:14:18,470 --> 00:14:20,534
But he had just been
kidnapped by a cartel.

396
00:14:20,536 --> 00:14:21,871
It happens down there.

397
00:14:21,873 --> 00:14:23,706
- They grab you, demand cash.
- I negotiated

398
00:14:23,708 --> 00:14:26,241
- with the cartel.
- I owe this man my life.

399
00:14:26,243 --> 00:14:28,374
He's one of the good guys, Jane.

400
00:14:28,376 --> 00:14:30,872
Why didn't you tell me any of this?

401
00:14:30,874 --> 00:14:32,874
Because the kidnappers demanded secrecy.

402
00:14:32,876 --> 00:14:34,709
They said they were gonna kill him.

403
00:14:34,711 --> 00:14:37,410
I need to talk to you about your brother.

404
00:14:37,412 --> 00:14:39,544
Absolutely. Satya.

405
00:14:40,447 --> 00:14:42,946
It means, "all in pursuit of truth."

406
00:14:42,948 --> 00:14:44,380
It's a part of my religion.

407
00:14:44,382 --> 00:14:45,680
I'm a Jain.

408
00:14:45,681 --> 00:14:50,381
_

409
00:14:50,481 --> 00:14:52,978
I just want to know what
happened to my brother.

410
00:14:55,814 --> 00:14:57,514
I'm sorry.

411
00:14:57,516 --> 00:14:58,848
L-look, I...

412
00:14:58,850 --> 00:15:00,216
I was looking for you.

413
00:15:00,218 --> 00:15:01,417
But I ran into Michael instead.

414
00:15:01,419 --> 00:15:02,851
I tried not to say anything,

415
00:15:02,853 --> 00:15:04,786
- but he just, he knows me so well.
- God.

416
00:15:04,788 --> 00:15:06,991
And I was scared.

417
00:15:06,993 --> 00:15:08,993
I thought that I just saw a dead man.

418
00:15:08,995 --> 00:15:10,628
And what were you doing even knocking

419
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:13,029
on the door in the first place, huh?

420
00:15:15,181 --> 00:15:16,449
I saw you come out,

421
00:15:16,451 --> 00:15:18,551
and you put a "do not disturb" sign on,

422
00:15:18,553 --> 00:15:20,218
and you had that weird call earlier,

423
00:15:20,220 --> 00:15:22,187
and I just...

424
00:15:22,189 --> 00:15:24,023
I thought that maybe
your father was in there.

425
00:15:24,025 --> 00:15:26,225
- What?
- But I didn't really think that.

426
00:15:26,227 --> 00:15:27,693
I just...

427
00:15:27,695 --> 00:15:29,227
I couldn't rule it out a hundred percent.

428
00:15:29,229 --> 00:15:30,295
Because you don't trust me.

429
00:15:30,297 --> 00:15:31,562
No, I do.

430
00:15:31,564 --> 00:15:32,996
Really?

431
00:15:32,998 --> 00:15:34,630
'Cause it doesn't feel like it.

432
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:40,466
Can we just talk about this later?

433
00:15:40,468 --> 00:15:43,100
I have to get my sister out
of the mental institution.

434
00:15:44,936 --> 00:15:47,074
All right, this is
how I'm gonna bust out.

435
00:15:47,076 --> 00:15:48,508
You know Dan, the hot delivery guy?

436
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:50,410
Yeah, I know, I don't see

437
00:15:50,412 --> 00:15:51,880
why everyone thinks he's so hot.

438
00:15:51,882 --> 00:15:53,516
- He's so basic.
- Anyway,

439
00:15:53,518 --> 00:15:54,717
every other Friday,

440
00:15:54,719 --> 00:15:56,583
Dan delivers supplies to our floor.

441
00:15:56,585 --> 00:15:57,850
And Nurse Chelsea...

442
00:15:57,852 --> 00:15:59,186
- _
- I know, she's so tragic,

443
00:15:59,188 --> 00:16:01,355
she just reeks of desperation.

444
00:16:01,357 --> 00:16:03,591
Anyway, she's always flirting with Dan.

445
00:16:03,593 --> 00:16:06,095
So all I have to do is sneak by them

446
00:16:06,097 --> 00:16:07,831
while Chelsea's distracted.

447
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:11,101
And then I can use Rose's brooch

448
00:16:11,103 --> 00:16:13,170
to pick the lock by the back door

449
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:15,971
and voilà... I'm free.

450
00:16:31,354 --> 00:16:33,888
Luisa?

451
00:16:35,190 --> 00:16:37,024
Hey,

452
00:16:37,026 --> 00:16:38,125
you.

453
00:16:38,127 --> 00:16:39,827
What are you doing here?

454
00:16:39,829 --> 00:16:42,832
I finally got power of attorney.

455
00:16:42,834 --> 00:16:44,867
I'm here to sign you out.

456
00:16:44,869 --> 00:16:47,838
Great.

457
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:49,908
Let's go back in this way.

458
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:52,712
It's a shortcut.

459
00:16:58,264 --> 00:16:59,829
Ah...

460
00:16:59,831 --> 00:17:02,764
We're all responsible
for our own baggage.

461
00:17:02,766 --> 00:17:05,598
At least that's what I
learned in the mental hospital.

462
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,501
- Luisa?
- What?

463
00:17:11,334 --> 00:17:13,266
Look, I don't know what
made you change your mind

464
00:17:13,268 --> 00:17:14,934
and decide to sign me out,

465
00:17:14,936 --> 00:17:17,169
- but I cannot believe that...
- Rose is Sin Rostro.

466
00:17:17,171 --> 00:17:18,702
Come again?

467
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,264
Rose, our stepmother...

468
00:17:22,573 --> 00:17:23,605
Is Sin Rostro.

469
00:17:23,607 --> 00:17:25,571
Sin Rostro,

470
00:17:25,573 --> 00:17:28,475
like, that crazy big drug-dealer person?

471
00:17:28,477 --> 00:17:30,876
Yeah, except she got out of drugs

472
00:17:30,878 --> 00:17:33,047
and now runs a plastic surgery ring

473
00:17:33,049 --> 00:17:35,609
that apparently changes criminals' faces.

474
00:17:36,521 --> 00:17:38,021
You don't say.

475
00:17:39,489 --> 00:17:42,126
Wow.

476
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:44,593
Sin Rostro, like, killed people, right?

477
00:17:44,595 --> 00:17:46,662
Only those who really deserved it.

478
00:17:46,664 --> 00:17:49,100
Lu, I am so sorry.

479
00:17:49,102 --> 00:17:51,503
And I believe you now.

480
00:17:51,505 --> 00:17:54,538
That's good, that's great.

481
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:55,874
Okay.

482
00:17:55,876 --> 00:17:57,509
I ran everything by your grandmother,

483
00:17:57,511 --> 00:18:00,444
and we both agreed that this
will be a dry baby shower.

484
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:03,983
Apparently, we feel
very strongly about this.

485
00:18:03,985 --> 00:18:05,853
It's really sweet what
you're doing for me, Lina.

486
00:18:05,855 --> 00:18:07,454
Are you kidding?

487
00:18:07,456 --> 00:18:09,088
Your best friend throws
you your baby shower,

488
00:18:09,090 --> 00:18:10,623
- that's the rule.
- I know,

489
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:12,992
but, you know, it's been
kind of weird with us.

490
00:18:12,994 --> 00:18:14,261
Since the whole Frankie thing.

491
00:18:14,263 --> 00:18:15,228
Yeah, I know.

492
00:18:15,230 --> 00:18:16,930
And I missed you.

493
00:18:16,932 --> 00:18:17,897
So...

494
00:18:17,899 --> 00:18:20,198
I missed you, too.

495
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:22,198
Okay, we'll hug it out later,

496
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,201
but we have things to accomplish here.

497
00:18:24,203 --> 00:18:26,771
Okay, did you finish
your target registry?

498
00:18:26,773 --> 00:18:28,709
- No.
- Jane.

499
00:18:28,711 --> 00:18:30,009
It's complicated.

500
00:18:30,011 --> 00:18:31,641
I mean, where are we gonna even live?

501
00:18:31,643 --> 00:18:33,709
Do we get two of everything
or one of everything?

502
00:18:33,711 --> 00:18:35,345
Hmm, I didn't think about that.

503
00:18:35,347 --> 00:18:37,045
Okay, we'll just say "cash."

504
00:18:37,047 --> 00:18:38,913
next up... Party game.

505
00:18:38,915 --> 00:18:40,914
- Oh, God, I hate party games.
- I know you don't like party games.

506
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:45,087
You'll just fill this
out about each other.

507
00:18:45,089 --> 00:18:46,354
Where did you meet?

508
00:18:46,356 --> 00:18:48,922
That'll be funny.

509
00:18:48,974 --> 00:18:51,812
Um, what's your favorite song?

510
00:18:51,814 --> 00:18:53,647
Oh, and, um, this is a good one...

511
00:18:53,649 --> 00:18:55,849
Which one of you will
be the disciplinarian?

512
00:19:16,207 --> 00:19:19,278
Luisa, there is so much I
want to say to you but can't.

513
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,015
So let me say this.

514
00:19:21,097 --> 00:19:23,096
I'm sorry that you were
hurt during all of this.

515
00:19:23,098 --> 00:19:25,634
And I know you have so many questions,

516
00:19:25,636 --> 00:19:27,470
so I want to answer one.

517
00:19:27,472 --> 00:19:29,372
Unfortunately, your father is

518
00:19:29,374 --> 00:19:31,873
where the lightning first struck,

519
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:33,810
where there were fireworks.

520
00:19:33,812 --> 00:19:35,779
Sounds like gibberish to me,

521
00:19:35,781 --> 00:19:37,861
but clearly it meant something to Luisa.

522
00:19:40,589 --> 00:19:42,423
Look, you were right.

523
00:19:42,425 --> 00:19:43,959
I shouldn't have knocked on that door,

524
00:19:43,961 --> 00:19:45,996
and I should have
trusted you enough to wait

525
00:19:45,998 --> 00:19:47,365
and ask you what was going on.

526
00:19:47,367 --> 00:19:49,836
But, I mean, can you blame me, really?

527
00:19:49,838 --> 00:19:51,571
I mean, with everything
that's going on...

528
00:19:51,573 --> 00:19:54,173
I mean, the murders and twins
and mastermind criminals,

529
00:19:54,175 --> 00:19:57,682
this is not normal stuff.
It's pretty friggin' crazy.

530
00:19:57,684 --> 00:20:00,053
Yeah, you're right.

531
00:20:00,055 --> 00:20:03,755
But even with all that, I
thought that you trusted me.

532
00:20:03,757 --> 00:20:06,492
And I do.

533
00:20:06,494 --> 00:20:08,596
For the most part.

534
00:20:08,598 --> 00:20:11,397
Ah, yeah, see, "for the most part"...

535
00:20:11,399 --> 00:20:12,831
